Honestly she already does really well. I'm honestly glad she got an opportunity to work at LMG like this! I've seen people get kinda angry about it because she was somewhat annoying in the ROG rig reboot video, but to me it seems like she was trying to play a character and just didn't do an _amazing_ job at it. From this video I can see that she's already a lot better at performing to camera, even in her first techlinked!


Edit: Also does anyone else feel like watching LMG feel like you're watching The Office, just a little less absurd and more computery; This is coming from someone that's never seen The Office before
